post_text:
As we transition on October 1st, 2020 to "in person" instruction in the North Franklin School District, the health and safety of your students is our top priority. One of the requirements for students to return to the building is that students and staff must be screened regularly for symptoms of COVID-19.

All students and staff will be required to take their temperature and answer some screening questions BEFORE they leave their homes each morning. Upon arrival at school, staff will double check temperatures as students and staff enter the building.

All parents will need to download the Skyward application on their phone or log in to the Skyward computer program to fill out an on-line “wellness screening” for this purpose. Parents can contact their school office secretary to get their username and password for Skyward.

https://www2.nerdc.wa-k12.net/scripts/cgiip.exe/WService=wnfranks71/seplog01.w

post_text: On September 14th, The Benton Franklin Health District recommended that the North Franklin School District plan for implementation of in-person hybrid learning as early as Oct.1, 2020. The NFSD will use a “Hybrid Model” and start school on Thursday, October 1st, 2020. As we planned earlier this summer, the hybrid model will consist of in person instruction every day for elementary students (Grades K-6) and a combination of in person and distance learning on a rotating basis for Secondary students (Grades 7-12).

The NFSD will use a “Hybrid Model” and start school on Thursday, October 1st, 2020. As we planned earlier this summer, the hybrid model will consist of in person instruction every day for elementary students (Grades K-6) and a combination of in person and distance learning on a rotating basis for Secondary students (Grades 7-12).

August 31 at 7:12 PM ·

This is it!
Schedules are on Skyward!

A few things to remember -- there are still some changes to be made as we balance classes, find mistakes, etc. This MAY NOT be the FINAL schedule for you. Make sure to check Skyward again before classes start on Tuesday, September 8.

Due to the current circumstances, we will be allowing very few schedule changes unless there is an error (i.e. missing a period, incorrect class for graduation requirements, etc.).

IF you have any change requests or don't have enough classes scheduled, use this Google Form to make any requests. We will not be accepting requests via phone, email, paper note or any other method. Not all change requests will be granted and all changes are subject to availability. Counselors will communicate with you via email.

https://forms.gle/bhidwhWbvc3WApfC9

Thank you Mid Columbia Libraries!!!

post_text: Thank you to Case Vandermuelen and Coulee Flats Dairy and JCs Mesa Grocery for supporting Mesa Mustangs!!! We appreciate having neighbors like you!!!
shared_text:
Coulee Flats Dairy
July 3 at 7:55 PM ·

Thank you friends for joining us in making June Dairy Month a platform for supporting our community! We are so excited to have a partner in the Dogra family, new owners of JC's Grocery, working to make this a great store for locals to pick up necessities--like milk!

Even in these unusual times, word got out, you participated, and 1,057 gallons of Darigold milk were sold! With JC's pledge to match our donation, over $2,000 will be donated to the Mesa Mustangs CPT to help fund Chromebooks for students.

Have a wonderful 4th of July! We feel fortunate to live and dairy farm here. Producing healthy dairy products and giving back to our local schools to strengthen our community gives us great purpose, and that means a lot these days!

post_text:
En Espanol -

La prioridad del Distrito Escolar de North Franklin es poner las necesidades de los estudiantes, las familias y el personal primero y la educación siempre. Somos una organización educativa, eso es lo que hacemos. Pero si no satisfacemos las necesidades de nuestros estudiantes, familias y personal, los humanos a los que servimos, no podremos cumplir nuestra misión. Para crear el mejor plan para reabrir las escuelas en el otoño, necesitamos que los estudiantes, las familias y el personal nos brinden su opinión para ayudarnos en nuestros esfuerzos de planificación. Gracias de antemano por participar en esta breve encuesta para ayudarnos a guiar nuestra toma de decisiones.

La encuesta cierra a las 5 p.m. el 7 de junio.

https://forms.gle/rjysXYTQipEgRwbVA

Pero si no satisfacemos las necesidades de nuestros estudiantes, familias y personal, los humanos a los que servimos, no podremos cumplir nuestra misión. Para crear el mejor plan para reabrir las escuelas en el otoño, necesitamos que los estudiantes, las familias y el personal nos brinden su opinión para ayudarnos en nuestros esfuerzos de planificación. Gracias de antemano por participar en esta breve encuesta para ayudarnos a guiar nuestra toma de decisiones.

La encuesta cierra a las 5 p.m. el 7 de junio.

https://forms.gle/rjysXYTQipEgRwbVA

post_text:
May 6, 2020 is “National School Nurse Day”, a time to celebrate our school district nurse, Erica Barragan! We’d like to take this opportunity to recognize Erica and acknowledge her role in the educational setting. Our community appreciates the contributions our school nurse makes every day to improve the health, safety, and academic success of our students.

The theme this year – “School Nurses: Supporting Students in Times of Crisis” – reinforces the changing times of 2020. This year, more than ever, all members of the NFSD Neighborhood, the school nurse included, have been required to take on unprecedented roles and adapt quickly to changes in their jobs. It is reflective of the significant role the school nurse has in the health care of their school communities to help make a healthier place for children and families to learn and grow during this crisis.

Thank you Erica Barragan!!!!

Shhhhhhhhhh, it's a secret!
Our teachers have had a dramatic change in their normal routine over the last several weeks and Teacher Appreciation Week is a perfect time to lift them up and tell them thanks! So, I have scheduled a time at each of the schools to offer them the same kind of service we have been offering our families over the last several weeks - a "drive through" teacher appreciation opportunity!! I have invited all of the teachers to drive through their school's bus loop following the schedule below so I can say thank you and present them with a small token of my appreciation. If you would like to join me, as long as you follow the social distancing guidelines, you are welcome to stand six feet apart and join me! If there is a specific teacher you want to see, you should invite them so they are sure to come!

Here is a map of the known free or open Wi-Fi Hotspots that are currently available for student use in the North Franklin School District - Click on the marked location for password or connection directions at each location. No matter which location you are using, please be polite, follow normal school internet use expectations, do your homework and communicate via email with your teachers, and follow social distancing guidelines. If you know of others, please let us know and we will add then to the map. If you or someone you know of is still struggling to find an internet connection, please contact your school office and let them know. Tell your friiends!!!!

Freshly made lunches are back at Connell High School!!!!! Those Spring Break, pre-made lunches were awesome, but Spring Break is over and our free sack breakfast/lunch meals for children aged 18 and under are available to pick up at Basin City Elementary, Mesa Elementary, Connell High School and Connell Elementary from 11:00 to 11:30 am, and in Eltopia at the intersection of 5th and Seattle from 12:00 to 12:30 pm on weekdays.

¡¡¡Los almuerzos recién hechos están de vuelta en Connell High School !!!!! Las vacaciones de primavera, los almuerzos precocinados fueron increíbles, pero las vacaciones de primavera terminaron y nuestras comidas de desayuno / almuerzo gratis para niños de 18 años y menores están disponibles para recoger en Basin City Elementary, Mesa Elementary, Connell High School y Connell Elementary de 11:00 a 11:30 am, y en Eltopia en la intersección de 5th y Seattle de 12:00 a 12:30 pm de lunes a viernes.

CHS Distance Learning Survey for Parents

Connell High School
April 11 at 12:47 AM ·

This is especially for parents of CHS students!!
🤩🤩🤩
As we work to adapt to a more comprehensive distance learning model, we need to collect some information from you. We have developed this survey that we are asking you to complete.
https://forms.gle/oZTCMRCkWrfJnNLc7

The survey needs to be completed only once by each family, even if you have multiple students at CHS.
We are asking that it is completed by Monday morning.

This link was also sent in an email to all CHS students, asking them to spend a few minutes with you this weekend to complete the survey. :)

Thank you!

Connell High School
April 6 at 3:00 PM ·

We have some ideas to help you explore the world while you stay home and stop the spread during Spring Break! How about a virtual visit to the San Diego Zoo? Or a tour of the Smithsonian's National Museum of Natural History?

You could also challenge friends, family members, or classmates to complete all the tasks on the NFSD Service Scavenger Hunt! Or you could play Eagle Bingo (thank you to senior Kennedy Syrie for creating the bingo card!).

What about catching up on the CharacterStrong 30 Days of Kindness Journal? All the challenges and the journal prompts are on the grade level Google Classrooms.

It's going to be beautiful outside this week! Get outside - go for a (socially distanced, of course) walk, a run, or bike ride. Enjoy the warm temps, get some Vitamin D, and breathe in the fresh air.

Stay Home, Stay Healthy Eagles! #CHSEaglesStrong

If your student or a student you know in Connell, Basin City or Eltopia needs internet access to download assignments or access their student email, the Mid Columbia Library branches’ wi-Fi is on and free. You may park or sit outside the building and use the wi-fi to download assignments and check email. Please remember to follow social distancing guidelines.

Si su estudiante o un estudiante que conoce en Connell, Basin City o Eltopia necesita acceso a Internet para descargar tareas o acceder al correo electrónico de su estudiante, el wifi de las sucursales de la Biblioteca de Mid Columbia está encendido y es gratuito. Puede estacionarse o sentarse fuera del edificio y usar el wi-fi para descargar tareas y consultar el correo electrónico. Recuerde seguir las pautas de distanciamiento social.

shared_text:
Connell High School is at Connell High School.
March 28 at 6:20 PM · Connell, WA ·

It's been two weeks since Governor Inslee directed the schools to close. Two weeks since the halls of CHS were filled with learning and laughter. Even though we are apart, we wanted to remind you that the teachers, administrators, counselors, and other support staff are here for you. Please reach out to us with questions, concerns, or just to say hi. We miss you!

We also wanted to remind you about some resources that are available to you!
+++++++++
Google Classrooms have been set up for each grade level as an additional way to share information and resources.
Students and Parents can both join!

Class codes are below.

Class of 2021: 5rkzquz
Class of 2022: kzq5zed
Class of 2023: co2lrlg

Parents -- need a tutorial on how to use Google Classroom? We've got you!
https://youtu.be/2Iowi-gmbys

Ask questions if you need help! We are here for you!

post_text:
The North Franklin School District will continue giving away free lunches for all children 18 years and under from 11:00-11:30 Monday through Friday. This is considered to be an essential service to our community during this stay at home order from the Governor. Pick up will be drive-through style in the bus loops at Connell Elementary, Mesa Elementary and Basin City elementary. It will be drive through at Connell High School behind the kitchen.



El Distrito Escolar North Franklin continuará regalando almuerzos gratis para todos los niños de 18 años y menores de 11: 00-11: 30 de lunes a viernes. Esto se considera un servicio esencial para nuestra comunidad durante esta orden de estadía en el hogar del Gobernador. La recogida será en el estilo de conducir en los bucles de autobús en la primaria Connell, la primaria Mesa y la primaria Basin City. Será conducido a través de Connell High School detrás de la cocina.

To assist our local communities with the school closures in our state related to the spread of COVID-19, Desert Winds Wireless is offering free wireless installation, and 2 months of our mid plan service complimentary to new customers with students in K-12 school or those who are in College.

We at Desert Winds Wireless are committed to assisting our state and local communities in helping to continue to educate our children and to keep families and businesses connected and working through this difficult time.

Please send us a message if you are interested in this.

post_text: The North Franklin School District is proud to celebrate Education Support Professionals Week Monday, March 9th through Friday, March 13th. A quality education for all students starts with a quality staff of education support professionals. From the bus driver who picks your child up in the morning and the mechanic who keeps the bus running, to the cook who makes them breakfast, the custodian who cleans up, the clerk who makes sure they have lunch money, the maintenance man who repairs the buildings, the secretary who manages kids and adults alike, the nurse who takes care of their "owies" and makes sure they are safe, the para-educator who teaches them in small group instruction, and the groundskeeper who makes sure the play fields are green and clean. This week we celebrate all of the hard working professionals who work day in and day out, behind the scenes, keeping the schools running and doing their part to make the NFSD neighborhood an incredible place for learning!

post_text: We have learned there was a presumptive case of COVID-19 (coronavirus) at Wildhorse resort in Pendleton, OR. An Individual staff member who has recently traveled to Wildhorse has contacted the District for guidance. NFSD officials contacted the Benton-Franklin Health District (BFHD) and BFHD says the risk to the public is minimal and they do not recommend any further action at this time. All staff and families are encouraged to continue to use good hygiene practices including frequent hand-washing and the use of alcohol-based hand sanitizer if soap and water are not available. Out of an abundance of caution, district custodial staff will continue to sanitize high-touch surfaces and known staff and student locations.
